[b]Relative Leg Efficiency[/b] scores each price leg — from pivot to pivot — on how efficiently price moved: how direct the path was, how fast, and how much counter-pressure it absorbed along the way.

[b]What it does[/b]

A high-efficiency leg moves cleanly in one direction without retracing. A low-efficiency leg covers the same distance but with heavy counter-pressure, slow momentum, or a winding path. The RLE score (0–100) captures this quality numerically, making it possible to compare legs across a chart and filter for the kinds of moves worth trading.

[b]Scoring components[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Path efficiency[/b] — Straight-line (air) distance vs. actual path distance traveled
[*][b]Time efficiency[/b] — Speed normalization or time penalty, user-selectable
[*][b]Counter-pressure[/b] — Measured by opposing candle count, body-weighted pressure, or both
[*][b]Live scoring[/b] — In-progress leg scored continuously from the current pivot to the active bar
[/list]

[b]Visualization[/b]

Leg lines and RLE labels are drawn directly on the chart at each pivot. The current in-progress score updates bar by bar.

